\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Expected sample size and sample size savings as a function of K (number of planned analyses) under delta = 0.5. The curve flattens rapidly: K = 20 captures approximately 90 percent of the savings available from fully sequential monitoring.}}{12}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
