\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Naive MLE bias at the stopping time as a function of K. More frequent monitoring increases the conditional bias at stopping because the test statistic is more likely to cross the boundary at an extreme point. The bias remains small in absolute terms but grows monotonically with K.}}{12}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:hf-bias-plot}{{4}{12}{Naive MLE bias at the stopping time as a function of K. More frequent monitoring increases the conditional bias at stopping because the test statistic is more likely to cross the boundary at an extreme point. The bias remains small in absolute terms but grows monotonically with K}{figure.caption.8}{}}
